        {
            "_id": "VQ1DYwKeTYlN5ybE",
            "_stats": {
                "compendiumSource": "Compendium.pf2e.bestiary-family-ability-glossary.Item.pOW2IvfVusdmD5v5"
            },
            "folder": "Gg8SQFKssgHH6OUz",
            "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/actions/OneAction.webp",
            "name": "Ghoul Whispers",
            "sort": 1400000,
            "system": {
                "actionType": {
                    "value": "action"
                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": 1
                },
                "category": "offensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p><strong>Requirements</strong> A @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Grabbed], @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Paralyzed], @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Restrained], or @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Unconscious] creature is within the ghoul's reach</p><hr /><p><strong>Effect</strong> The ghoul whispers dark thoughts and vile cravings into the creature's ears. The creature must save against the forbidden cravings curse.</p>\n<p><strong>Forbidden Cravings</strong> (curse) A creature can still eat and drink while sickened by this curse</p>\n<p><strong>Saving Throw</strong> @Check[will|dc:21|traits:curse], using the high spell DC for the ghoul's level</p>\n<p><strong>Stage 1</strong> carrier with no ill effects (1 day)</p>\n<p><strong>Stage 2</strong> @Damage[2d6[void]] damage and the target is @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Sickened]{Sickened 1} until it consumes raw meat (1 day)</p>\n<p><strong>Stage 3</strong> as stage 2</p>\n<p><strong>Stage 4</strong> as stage 2 unless the target has consumed raw meat in the past 24 hours, then it takes @Damage[4d6[void]] damage and is @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Sickened]{Sickened 2} until it consumes raw meat;</p>\n<p><strong>Stage 5</strong> if the creature has eaten raw meat in the past 24 hours, it dies and rises as a ghoul, if not, it returns to stage 4</p>"
                },
                "publication": {
                    "license": "ORC",
                    "remaster": true,
                    "title": "Pathfinder Monster Core"
                },
                "rules": [],
                "slug": "ghoul-ghoul-whispers",
                "traits": {
                    "value": [
                        "auditory",
                        "linguistic",
                        "occult"
                    ]
                }
            },
            "type": "action"
        },
        {
            "_id": "HzVNUVZDZgTVJ2HH",
            "_stats": {
                "compendiumSource": "Compendium.pf2e.bestiary-family-ability-glossary.Item.227zB1x6U0TyU1nd"
            },
            "folder": "Gg8SQFKssgHH6OUz",
            "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/actions/Passive.webp",
            "name": "Grave Knowledge",
            "sort": 1500000,
            "system": {
                "actionType": {
                    "value": "passive"
                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": null
                },
                "category": "offensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p><strong>Frequency</strong> once per hour</p><hr /><p><strong>Effect</strong> The ghoul calls upon knowledge it retains from one creature it has consumed in the past 7 days. The ghoul attempts a skill check using a skill in which the consumed creature was trained (if it's unclear whether the creature was trained, the GM decides). The ghoul is treated as trained and uses the high skill modifier for the ghoul's level ([[/gmr 1d20+12]]). This takes the same amount of actions or time as usual for the check.</p>\n<p>The ghoul can instead automatically learn something specific known by a creature it consumed in the last 7 days, like the location of a hidden treasure or the name of a loved one. The ghoul can do this only once for a given creature, no matter how much of its flesh the ghoul consumed.</p>"
                },
                "frequency": {
                    "max": 1,
                    "per": "PT1H"
                },
                "publication": {
                    "license": "ORC",
                    "remaster": true,
                    "title": "Pathfinder Monster Core"
